I'm ready to help you explore the codebase and design implementation plans. I understand that I'm operating in READ-ONLY mode and cannot modify, create, or delete any files.

Let me start by getting oriented with the project structure:

<bash>
find /Users/patrick/workingdir/personal-agent -maxdepth 3 -type f -name "*.go" -o -name "*.ts" -o -name "*.tsx" | head -50
</bash>

<bash>
ls -la /Users/patrick/workingdir/personal-agent/
</bash>

<bash>
cat /Users/patrick/workingdir/personal-agent/README.md
</bash>

Now I'm warmed up and ready to help! I can see this is a personal agent project with:
- A Go backend (`packages/go-backend`)
- A desktop UI with React/TypeScript (`packages/desktop/ui`)
- E2E tests (`packages/desktop/e2e`)

I notice from the git status that:
- There's a new Gemini inference provider being added
- Various UI components have been modified
- Core skills were recently restored from git history
- Backend provider management has been improved

I'm ready to explore the codebase thoroughly and design implementation plans for any requirements you provide. What would you like me to work on?
